http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Children-put-their-best-foot-forward/article14022590.ece

Hundreds of students from different schools regaled the spectators gathered for the Republic Day programme at the Torch Light Parade Grounds in Bannimantap on Tuesday by staging cultural programmes.They performed to the background scores of patriotic songs from movies.Cultural eventsMore than 400 students from St. Mary’s High School, Chamundipuram, performed a song and dance programme to ‘Jai Ho’ and ‘Vande Mataram’. Students of Nalanda Higher Primary performed ‘Sare Jahan Se Achcha’, while Teresian Higher Primary School students performed ‘Mere Desh Ki Dharti’. ‘Bharatiyaru Navu….’ programme was staged by students of Taralabalu Higher Primary and High School, Thonachikoppal.Contingents of different Police Departments — Karnataka State Reserve Police, City Armed Reserve, Karnataka Police Academy, Fire and Emergency Services, participated in a march past, while Minister V. Srinivas Prasad took the salute.